It appears that something changed in Spring. This code didn&#39;t used to cause Spring to complain if the two directories specified in the `spring.config.additional-location` system property didn&#39;t exist.  Now it does. Thankfully, Spring provides a way to mark these directories as optional, like this:

    String homeDir = System.getProperty(&quot;user.home&quot;);
    String value = &quot;optional:{H}/spring/config/,optional:{H}/spring/,optional:{H}/&quot;.replace(&quot;{H}&quot;, homeDir);
    System.setProperty(&quot;spring.config.additional-location&quot;, value);

