In your class `Error` you have annoated the properties
`type` and `message` with `@XmlAttribute`.
That means, you can handle XML input with XML *attributes*, like this:

    &lt;error type=&quot;MalformedXML&quot; message=&quot;Message&quot;&gt;&lt;/error&gt;

But actually you have input with XML *elements*, like this:

	&lt;error&gt;
		&lt;type&gt;MalformedXML&lt;/type&gt;
		&lt;message&gt;Message 1&lt;/message&gt;
	&lt;/error&gt;

So, in your class `Error` you need to replace `@XmlAttribute` by
`@XmlElement`, or just omit it altogether.

After doing this, the `&lt;error&gt;` parts of your XML input
will be unmarshalled correctly.

